title: Jessica Tuki
text:
Jessica Tuki (born 28 October 1987 in <a href="New%20Plymouth">New Plymouth</a>, <a href="Taranaki">Taranaki</a>) is a former <a href="New%20Zealand">New Zealand</a> professional <a href="netball">netball</a> and basketball player. She played for the <a href="Northern%20Mystics">Northern Mystics</a> in the <a href="ANZ%20Championship">ANZ Championship</a> and was previously in the <a href="New%20Zealand%20national%20netball%20team">Silver Ferns</a> in 2006. Tuki replaced <a href="Jodi%20Brown">Jodi Brown</a> in the team to go to the <a href="2006%20Commonwealth%20Games">2006 Commonwealth Games</a> in <a href="Melbourne">Melbourne</a>, after Brown injured her knee. She has previously played for the <a href="Western%20Flyers">Western Flyers</a> (2004–05) and the <a href="Otago%20Rebels">Otago Rebels</a> (2006) in the <a href="National%20Bank%20Cup">National Bank Cup</a>. She also trialled for the Tall Ferns basketball team.
During the ANZ Championship era, Tuki has played in almost every position except for Centre.
